        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Went through a couple variations of this to resolve #34007. Settled on just emitting an empty `msg_show` event rather than `msg_clear(reason)`. I think just emitting an empty message event should be OK. The others were a bit difficult to document/reason about. I don't think it would make sense for `:echo \"\"` to clear message from a dedicated message window, just the cmdline. So a more ambiguous event seems desirable.",
